      • add

        public SortLevel add(int columnRowIndex)
        Adds a new SortLevel applied to a column (or a row, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) with the specified index into the SortLevelCollection.
        Parameters:
        columnRowIndex - Index of the column (or the row, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) relative to the range that an added SortLevel applies to.
        Returns:
        A new SortLevel applied to a column (or a row, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) with the specified index relative to the range.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - columnRowIndex is less than zero or is equal to or greater than width (or height, if SortState.isLeftToRight() is true) of the range.
        IllegalArgumentException - Column/row at the specified index is being sorted by the same criteria more than once. Delete the duplicate sort criteria and try again.
